![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5e0766f3-fe99-4c0c-aeb1-ae9454b20b1c/209.jpg)

Arguably the biggest movie of 2021, Spider-Man No Way Home definitely had the unenviable task of meeting all of our expectations whilst moving the narrative forward for the MCU version of Spider-Man. Packed with awesome moments, insane cameos, and touching callbacks, some are calling the film the best Spider-Man film to date but how good was it... really? Join The Don and Cloudis Maximus as they open a portal and let in their inner fanboy in this in-depth, spoiler filled review of Spider-Man No Way Home!  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
